HEADWORD: Wisse
<hw>Wis"se</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>w⟦imac⟧sian</ets>. See <er>Wise</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>To
show; to teach; to inform; to guide; to direct.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ere we depart I shall thee so well <qex>wisse</qex>⟦br⟧
That of mine house ne shalt thou never misse.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

